permissions:
  default: ask
jinx_name: py
description: Execute a short Python snippet. The code is passed verbatim to exec(). Set the "output" variable to a result string. Do not write print statements. Keep snippets simple and self-contained. Every opened block (if/for/while/try/except/def/with/class) must have a non-empty indented body, even if just `pass`. `try:` must be followed by `except:`. Match parentheses, brackets, and braces carefully. os.walk returns a 3-tuple `(root, dirs, files)`; unpack it as exactly three names or iterate without unpacking. Verify a value is iterable before looping over it. Use raw strings (r"...") or forward slashes for Windows-style paths.
inputs:
- code
steps:
- code: '{{code}}'
  engine: python
